}{\plain \fs24 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b 107.}{\plain \fs24   Francesca, whose chief rhetorical strategy is to remove as much blame from herself \softline
as she is able, finding other forces at fault wherever possible (e.g., Paolo's physical beauty, her \softline
despicable husband, the allure of a French romance), here tries to even the score with her \softline
husband.  She may be damned, but he, as the killer of his wife and brother, will be much lower \softline
down, in the ninth circle.  Since Gianciotto, who killed them in 1283-84, lived until 1304, his \softline
shade could not be seen by Dante in Caina.  We have, as a result, no basis on which to question \softline
her opinion.  However, had Dante wanted to guarantee it, it would have taken a line or so to do \softline
just that -- and he does several times have sinners tell of the impending arrival of still others in a \softline
given circle in ways that clearly call for acceptance (see the note to }{\plain \fs24 \i Inf}{\plain \fs24 . XXXII.54-69).  And so \softline
we are left wondering at Francesca's remark, and should at least keep this question open.  It \softline
seems better to view her prediction as a wish stated as a fact than as a fact.  This is to support the \softline
interpretation of Pier Angelo Perotti, "Caina attende," }{\plain \fs24 \i L'Alighieri}{\plain \fs24  2 (1993), pp. 129-34.  \softline
However, for an example of the continuing view that accepts Francesca's predictive placement of \softline
her husband in hell see Ignazio Baldelli, "Dante, i Guidi e i Malatesta," }{\plain \fs24 \i Annali della Scuola \softline
Normale Superiore di Pisa}{\plain \fs24 , serie 3, 18 (1988), p. 1070, a judgment that he has reaffirmed in \softline
}{\plain \fs24 \i Dante e Francesca}{\plain \fs24  (Ravenna: Longo, 1999), pp. 55-56.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \tab Iannucci suggests that Gianciotto may have been conceived by Dante as being misshapen \softline
and lame like Vulcan, the cuckolded husband of Venus (see his "Forbidden Love: Metaphor and \softline
History," }{\plain \fs24 \i Annali della Facolt{\f2 \'42} di}{\plain \fs24  }{\plain \fs24 \i Lettere e Filosofia, Universit{\f2 \'42} di Siena}{\plain \fs24  11 [1980], p. 345).\par
